{"variables": [], "instructions": [], "planning": "- Overview\n  The function block `DLOG_DINT` is designed to log and store integer values along with related information, supporting a trigger mechanism based on incremental changes. It utilizes a circular buffer (`UNI_CIRCULAR_BUFFER`) to store data and decides whether to log new entries based on the input delta value.\n\n- Variable Definitions\n  The code defines the following types of variables:\n  - Input/Output Variables: `X`, a derived type `DLOG_DATA`, used to manage and store log data.\n  - Input Variables: `VALUE` (integer value), `COLUMN` (string, length 40), `DELTA` (integer delta value).\n  - Internal Variables: `UCB` (derived type `UNI_CIRCULAR_BUFFER`, for data storage), `id` (word integer, data identifier), `delta_last` (last delta value), `value_last` (last recorded value).\n\n- Main Logic Section\n  -- REGION CASE Statement\n     This section processes different operation modes via a `CASE` statement, with the following logic:\n     - 01: Increments `X.ID_MAX` and sets `id` to `WORD#16#0801`.\n     - 02: Stores the `COLUMN` string into `UCB.D_STRING`, sets `UCB.D_HEAD` to `id` and `UCB.D_MODE` to 1, then invokes the `UCB` function block to store the data.\n     - 03: Converts the previous value `value_last` to a string, stores it in `UCB.D_STRING`, sets `UCB.D_HEAD` to `id` and `UCB.D_MODE` to 1, then calls `UCB` to store the data. Simultaneously, updates `delta_last` to `value_last`.\n     - 04: Checks if the delta value `DELTA` is non-zero. If true, it verifies whether the current value `VALUE` exceeds the delta range of `delta_last` (i.e., `VALUE <= (delta_last - DELTA)` or `VALUE >= (delta_last + DELTA)`). If conditions are met, sets `X.ADD_DATA_REQ` to `TRUE` to indicate new data should be added and updates `delta_last` to the current `VALUE`.\n\n  -- REGION Update Previous Value\n     After processing the `CASE` statement, updates `value_last` to the current `VALUE` for use in the next cycle.",